 a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice De Uvedale was born in 1351, in Surrey, England, United Kingdom, her father, Thomas de Uvedale, was 46 and her mother, Benedicta De Shelving, was 12. She married Ralph De Shelton IV about 1373, in Monyash, Derbyshire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She was buried in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1351–":"1351–Surnud","1351–Female":"1351–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1361–1424":"1361–1424","1373–1421":"1373–1421","1373–Male":"1373–Surnud","1375–1421":"1375–1421","1375–1478":"1375–1478","1305–1365":"1305–1365","1340–1391":"1340–1391","1351":"1351","1373":"1373","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1361":"1361","1391":"1391","1305":"1305","1424":"1424","1478":"1478","1421":"1421","1365":"1365","1375":"1375","23 April 1375":"23. aprill 1375","about 1375":"umbes 1375","about 1373":"umbes 1373","Monyash, Derbyshire, England":"Monyash, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Surrey, England, United Kingdom":"Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shelton, Norfolkshire, England":"Shelton, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1351–":"1351–Kuollut","1351–Female":"1351–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1361–1424":"1361–1424","1373–1421":"1373–1421","1373–Male":"1373–Kuollut","1375–1421":"1375–1421","1375–1478":"1375–14